# What is a Delegate?

A **Delegate** is an object that holds a reference to a method. It allows you to pass methods as arguments to other methods.

```csharp
// 1. Declare
public delegate void Notify(string message);

// 2. Instantiate
Notify myDelegate = MyMethod;

// 3. Invoke
myDelegate("Hello!");
```

# Concise Code 🤏

Instead of defining a whole method, use Lambdas.

```csharp
// Old way
delegate int Square(int x);
Square s = GetSquare;

// Lambda way
Square s = (x) => x * x;

Console.WriteLine(s(5)); // 25
```
The `=>` operator is read as "goes to".

# Something Happened! 📢

**Events** allow a class to notify other classes when something interesting occurs (like a button click).

It is based on the Publisher-Subscriber model.

```csharp
public class Button {
    // Declare event
    public event EventHandler Clicked;

    public void Press() {
        // Raise event
        if (Clicked != null) Clicked(this, EventArgs.Empty);
    }
}
```

